data.name: 0000 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: All of us went to the library, except for Asahina who had gone to get the key.

data.name: 0001 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If we keep Haruhi focused on reading, we might not need to go to the music room.

data.name: 0002 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Okay, well let's split up and look for info about the music room and musicians!

data.name: 0003 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi was trying to liven everyone up, but it wasn't working on me.

data.name: 0004 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: We'd be able to find that stuff out so much easier with a simple online search.

data.name: 0005 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi hasn't realized that.

data.name: 0006 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If we search for materials here, she might forget about the music room at some point.

data.name: 0007 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Kyon, I wanna help.

data.name: 0009 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: You you want to search books with me?

data.name: 0010 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Yes, I'll help!

data.name: 0011 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I could relax if I were leaving her with Asahina, but I can't say the same for Haruhi.

data.name: 0012 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: No, you can read a book or something over there.

data.name: 0013 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: But I wanna help Haru-nyan...

data.name: 0014 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Look, I'll look after her so you get on and search!

data.name: 0015 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Yeah yeah.

data.name: 0016 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Yuki, investigate in order from the back-- Koizumi from the right--Kyon from the left.

data.name: 0018 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: The little sister and I will start our attack from the center.

data.name: 0019 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Understood, Miss Suzumiya.

data.name: 0020 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: In other words, I can have a strategy talk with Koizumi or Nagato without Haruhi seeing.

data.name: 0021 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Who should I talk to?

data.name: 0023 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, mind if I ask what you're thinking of doing here?

data.name: 0024 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Preferred action is to observe Haruhi Suzumiya's movement and act flexibly.

data.name: 0025 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: So nothing in particular then... Haruhi does always act on a whim after all.

data.name: 0026 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It's because she's always changing her plans that I'm always ending up in a panic.

data.name: 0027 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: …Take this.

data.name: 0028 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: A "#P05notepad#P00"? What do you want me to do with this?

data.name: 0029 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: If information confuses you, write it down in here.

data.name: 0030 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Ah, thanks.

data.name: 0031 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'll take it, but I'm not sure what I should write.

data.name: 0032 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Am I supposed to use it for marking Haruhi's grades or something?

data.name: 0034 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Koizumi, can I ask you what you're gonna be doing from here on?

data.name: 0035 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: We're more or less looking for books that grab Miss Suzumiya's attention, are we not?

data.name: 0036 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Well, that's part of why we're here, but don't you have a more concrete plan?

data.name: 0037 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: For now, we'll observe Miss Suzumiya's activity while looking for books that may interest her.

data.name: 0038 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Ah that's right, I shall offer you this.

data.name: 0039 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: A "#P05sticky note#P00?" What am I supposed to do with this?

data.name: 0040 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: If you find anything interesting, you should stick this on the page.

data.name: 0041 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Good point. There's no way I can fold or tear the pages after all…

data.name: 0043 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Oi, Kyon!

data.name: 0044 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Wh-what?

data.name: 0045 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: What are you doing messing everything up?!

data.name: 0046 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Look, I'm just searching for materials, r-right…?

data.name: 0047 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: That's not your position!

data.name: 0048 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Good grief, just be quiet and search for those materials, okay?

data.name: 0049 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Yeah yeah, silence in the library, right.

data.name: 0050 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Exactly, if you're noisy you're a nuisance to others.

data.name: 0051 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hey, even you're loud as you say that.

data.name: 0053 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Haru-nyan, it says to be quiet on that wall over there.

data.name: 0054 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Oh, right... I'd better be quiet.

data.name: 0055 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: She obeyed that surprisingly easily, right?

data.name: 0056 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Maybe she was focusing too much on the books and forgot about her surroundings?

data.name: 0057 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Look, just get on with it and search the materials--

data.name: 0058 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Sure sure.

data.name: 0059 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Maybe I'm just not used to Haruhi whispering, but that made my back tingle.

data.name: 0060 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Well though, tell me to search materials all you want, but I'm still not sure...

data.name: 0061 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: It'd help if she showed interest in anything other than the music room…

data.name: 0062 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Though, changing her interest might just get us involved in other troublesome phenomena.

data.name: 0063 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Fix one problem and you create another.

data.name: 0066 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I could search for books as much as I want, but I'm not gonna find any useful information.

data.name: 0067 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Besides, I'm in charge of the social studies & humanities shelves--nothing to do with music.

data.name: 0068 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: …I wonder if Nagato or Koizumi have found anything promising?

data.name: 0069 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Maybe I should sneak over and ask them?

data.name: 0070 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nagato, have you found any good info?

data.name: 0071 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: I selected deeply interesting literature and recorded it on a note.

data.name: 0072 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: That's good. Anything about musicians?

data.name: 0073 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Ghost stories. As long as it takes Haruhi Suzumiya's interest out of the school, it will do.

data.name: 0074 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: If we move to one of those, we'll have to call off the training camp, right?

data.name: 0075 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: The information is predominantly urban legend based, so pinpointing a location is difficult.

data.name: 0076 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: I see.

data.name: 0077 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: Here are the notes I put together.

data.name: 0078 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: "#P05Notes of short ghost stories#P00," huh… Is it okay if I take these?

data.name: 0079 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: It's fine. I've memorized them.

data.name: 0080 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I think Nagato is absolutely right, but I'm just doubtful these would interest Haruhi enough.

data.name: 0082 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Koizumi, have you found anything promising?

data.name: 0083 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: I'm afraid I'm at a complete loss.

data.name: 0084 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: It's rare to see you throwing up your hands when you're usually so faultless.

data.name: 0085 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Are you only faultless when it's uncalled-for?

data.name: 0086 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: I thought we could tackle unnatural phenomena with sci-fi, so I present you this.

data.name: 0087 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: A "#P05note of sci-fi shorts#P00"? What?

data.name: 0088 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: It's a note of excerpts from sci-fi novels I believe Miss Suzumiya will find interesting.

data.name: 0089 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Rather than tackling ghost stories with ghost stories, I wondered if sci-fi was better.

data.name: 0090 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Are you trying to counter it with that feeling of an unrealistic setting?

data.name: 0091 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Our problem is directing Miss Suzumiya's interest away from the school, after all.

data.name: 0092 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Well, it sounds reasonable, but I don't know if it's gonna work so easily.

data.name: 0094 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Oi, Kyon! You've been doing nothing but hanging around for ages!

data.name: 0095 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Are you making good progress with your research?

data.name: 0096 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Nope, with such an unclear task I don't feel like I'm making any progress at all.

data.name: 0097 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I knew it, Kyon will always be Kyon!

data.name: 0098 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Well I'm certainly me—you said that like you have a problem with it.

data.name: 0099 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: I've found plenty of interesting information!

data.name: 0100 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Hey, this is a library you know... You should be a little quieter.

data.name: 0101 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: There's not even anyone else here--it's fine--and anyway it's really interesting!

data.name: 0102 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I dunno what you found, but you're awfully enthusiastic about it, huh.

data.name: 0103 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: There may be no students, but if you make too much noise, the librarian will come flying.

data.name: 0104 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: But look, I have info on famous musicians who came from North High.

data.name: 0105 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Is it reliable?

data.name: 0106 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Probably.

data.name: 0107 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: When you say "probably," how much of it is true, and how much is your imagination?

data.name: 0108 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Look, Haru-nyan. This book's picture looks like this school.

data.name: 0109 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Great work, little sis! This is undoubtedly a picture of North High!

data.name: 0111 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Our brigade chief was ecstatic looking at the picture my little sister found.

data.name: 0112 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Though I can feel an aura coming from the librarian's booth telling us to be quiet...

data.name: 0113 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I don't want to have to deal with this tense atmosphere.

data.name: 0114 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Look, isn't this amazing, Kyon?!

data.name: 0115 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Wh-what?

data.name: 0116 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: We found something from twenty years ago!

data.name: 0117 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: And? What's it say?

data.name: 0118 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: It's not an article, it's a photo, but look how good the school building looks!

data.name: 0119 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Don't raise your voice over a meaningless article. I can feel the tension of the librarian.

data.name: 0120 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I'd feel better if we just got told off.

data.name: 0121 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Haru-nyan, there was this as well.

data.name: 0122 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Wow, what a discovery! Kyon, you should learn from your little sister!

data.name: 0123 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Yeah, whatever you say. More importantly--be quiet.

data.name: 0124 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Haruhi won't stop complaining about me, and I feel like the librarian is about to boil over.

data.name: 0125 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I've gained a newfound respect for those who came up with, "walking on a bed of nails."

data.name: 0126 (406.ja) KYON_SIS (妹)
data.value: Huh...? Isn't that Mikuru coming from the other side?

data.name: 0127 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Ah, Mikuru! Nice job! You got us the key, right!

data.name: 0128 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Don't raise your voice. She stood up so fast her chair fell and made a loud noise.

data.name: 0129 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Mikuru! Over here!!

data.name: 0131 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Oh no, I feel a sinister presence coming from the librarian's booth.

data.name: 0132 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: If we stay here too much longer I don't think I'll be able to breathe.

data.name: 0133 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Shall we head to the music room?

data.name: 0134 (406.ja) NAGATO (長門)
data.value: …Is that okay?

data.name: 0135 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: I understand your concern, but…

data.name: 0136 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: If we stay here any longer, I think a hole will open in my stomach from stress.

data.name: 0137 (406.ja) HARUHI (ハルヒ)
data.value: Mikuru, over here!

data.name: 0138 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: We need to get this noise generator out of here as soon as possible.

data.name: 0139 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I feel like the librarian might ban us from entering.

data.name: 0140 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Let's get out of here, Koizumi.

data.name: 0141 (406.ja) KOIZUMI (古泉)
data.value: Understood.

data.name: 0142 (406.ja) KYON (キョン)
data.value: Haruhi, let's go to the music room.

data.name: 0143 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: I wonder if this decision will work out in our favor or not.

data.name: 0144 (406.ja) MONOLOGUE (モノロ)
data.value: Maybe I should've read a book on fortune telling while I was here.

data.name: 0145 (406.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Talk with Nagato

data.name: 0146 (406.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Talk with Koizumi

data.name: 0147 (406.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Ask Nagato

data.name: 0148 (406.ja) INFO (CHOICE)
data.value: Ask Koizumi
